<TITLE> 1 dead after trawler sinks in Turag </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 1 (bdnews24.com)  One body was recovered and five people were missing after a trawler bearing some 40 homebound Ijtema passengers capsized Sunday in the Turag river, said police. The trawler began sinking after being rammed by another vessel near Kaundia Ghat next to Mirpur Embankment at around 3:30pm, deputy police commissioner of Mirpur Anwar Hossain told bdnews24.com. The other passengers, who managed to swim to shore, said they found six of their companions missing. bdnews24.com correspondent Golam Mortaza Antu said a team of divers from the Fire Service and Civil Defence launched a rescue mission and recovered the body of an unidentified boy at the spot. The trawler was heading to Gabtoli with homebound Ijtema passengers on board when another larger trawler slammed it from behind, said Hossain. Police detained the larger vessel and its driver from Aminbazar, who confessed to crashing into the passenger boat. bdnews24.c
